Package org.keycloak.models.map.storage.jpa.realm.entity

Class JpaComponentEntity

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.keycloak.models.map.common.UpdatableEntity.Impl
      • org.keycloak.models.map.storage.jpa.realm.entity.JpaComponentEntity
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, AbstractEntity, UpdatableEntity, MapComponentEntity, JpaRootEntity, JpaRootVersionedEntity
    @Entity
public class JpaComponentEntity
extends UpdatableEntity.Impl
implements MapComponentEntity, JpaRootVersionedEntity
    JPA MapComponentEntity implementation. Some fields are annotated with @Column(insertable = false, updatable = false) to indicate that they are automatically generated from json fields. As such, these fields are non-insertable and non-updatable.

    Components are independent (i.e. a component doesn't depend on another component) and can be manipulated directly via the component endpoints. Because of that, this entity implements JpaRootVersionedEntity instead of JpaChildEntity. This prevents OptimisticLockExceptions when different components in the same realm are being manipulated at the same time - for example, when multiple components are being added to the realm by different threads.

    By implementing JpaRootVersionedEntity, this entity will enforce optimistic locking, which can lead to OptimisticLockException if more than one thread attempts to modify the same component at the same time.

    Author:
    Stefan Guilhen
